# Workflow Gate Invocation

## Rule
Every response from the main agent MUST follow the `prodops-workflow-gate` skill (`.cursor/skills/prodops-workflow-gate/SKILL.md`).

## Step 0.5 first — detect intent, then run its step set:

### Intent `ticket_op` (a Jira ticket to action):
0. Greeting (first message only)
1. Ticket Intake
2. Validation (consult validator-agent)
3. Triage (consult triage-agent)
4. Solution Search (consult solution-agent)
5. Judge (consult judge-agent)
6. Comment (format and post)

### Intent `knowledge_query` (a general question, no ticket):
0. Greeting (first message only)
K1. Query Intake (parse question + entities; check `config/knowledge-faq.yaml`)
K2. Knowledge Search (skill: knowledge-expansion, + solution-agent) — exhaust sources
K3. Judge (consult judge-agent — knowledge_query scorecard)
K4. Answer (Knowledge-Answer format)

## No partial runs:
- If the user asks "just validate this ticket," still run Steps 1–6 internally but only surface the validation section in the comment.
- Internal steps are never skipped; only the visible output may be scoped.
- For `knowledge_query`, Validation and Triage are N/A (no ticket) — this is the only
  sanctioned skip; K2 (search) and K3 (judge) are still mandatory.
